VirtIfAuthType.description: The authentication type specified for a virtual interface.  Note that this object can be used to engage in significant attacks against an OSPF router.

VirtIfNeighbor.description: The Router ID of the virtual neighbor.

VirtIfRetransInterval.description: The number of seconds between link state avertisement retransmissions

VirtIfRtrDeadInterval.description: The number of seconds that a router's Hello packets have not been seen before its neighbors declare the router down.  This should be some multiple of the Hello interval.  This value must be the same for the virtual neighbor.

VirtIfTransitDelay.description: The estimated number of seconds it takes to transmit a Link State update packet over this interface.  Note that the minimal value SHOULD be 1 second.
